I’ve always dreamt of this version of myself and yet I don’t give myself enough credit because I’m still not where I want to be. As I sit with self (often🍄) I understand it’s the ego in me that always want more. I’ve attached myself to the emotions of wanting more not realizing I’ve already given myself more. I never thought I’d ever be this girl that is disciplined enough to go to the gym 5 times a week, learn new skills and explore and heal my inner child. I’ve hidden behind my potential of being greater than all the trials that have been thrown my way. If you name it I’ve probably been through it but I AM A WARRIOR. I may bend but i’ll never break 🤍 

Huge shoutout to @_shekem_ for this past month of patience and training/teaching me Muay Thai. This is something I always imagined learning and being great at. Still learning and becoming better by the day 🫶🏽

social_posts.post_text:
If you live in LA and aren’t afraid to hike 1300 feet up def check this trail out. I hike and go on trails a lot but never have I done something like this. I’m really doing any + everything that makes my soul happy!!

Year 32✨ 
Happy Bearthday to me🌸
This year is so special + dear to me. 
I’ve finally discovered who I am, what I want and am going for it. I stopped looking at everything I don’t have and started appreciating + being grateful for all that I do have. 
God, my Son, my health, family, my tribe (you know who you are), friends, my vision, purpose + my job. I’ve created boundaries for myself, I pushed myself to understand that people are people and if i lead with love + light there could be nothing a person can do to harm me. I’m breaking generational curses that were set out to destroy me by just loving myself and understanding that God lives within and all the love I ever wanted was inside of me. Year 32 this one is personal. I can’t wait to take you all on adventures with me as I discover more about myself + the world around me✨ 
Thank you for all the love my soul is so fulfilled 🫶🏽🤍

Colombia holds a special place in my heart🤍🌷

Part 1: This past week has been one I will never forget. I arrived to Colombia by myself and left with family + an experience I will never forget. As I cry writing this I know I can’t ever be who I was before august 1st. My entire life has changed in a week and I’m so grateful for every person in these photos (including myself) for making this happen. 2 nights of yage’ (ayahuasca) and I released over 25 years of trauma that was built up inside me.
I spoke to GOD.. C’mon MEEE? Little ole me🥹
I was able to experience the creator through vibrations, sounds, messages, and visions. I saw myself in a past life and so much more I can’t even begin to explain. I feel so honored and beyond grateful to have been able to be apart of something so sacred. My ancestors are beyond proud of me. I am so powerful and I truly understand what it takes to fully embrace that. 
My soul is fulfilled, my inner child is crying tears of joy, I am full of gratitude, love and peace. 
I am free! 
THIS IS ONLY THE BEGINNING💕
WOWW Guasca Colombia🇨🇴

LIFE UPDATE🤍

The integration period… 3 months post ayahuasca. 

i haven’t been too active on here because I’m figuring out how I want to reintroduce myself after experiencing an amazing rebirth. 

In just a couple weeks I will be a licensed mindset/life + manifestation coach🎉! 

I feel amazing!!! As I’m getting closer + closer to where I want to be and I have to blame a lot on changing my mindset. I have noticed feeling/being in a state of lack will manifest. Whether it’s lack of trust for myself, money, love, purpose etc you have to switch it up. Tell yourself everyday you lack NOTHING. You have everything you need and list them out one by one. 
Look at yourself in the mirror and hype yourself up! Brag about all the great things happening and the things to come as if they’re already here in existence. No need to be humble because we don’t want a humble mindset. 

The work starts from within.
You lack not a thing. You hold the power. Everything you want you can have trust and believe in yourself 🤍🦋

SWITZER FALLS🤍

If you know me you know I love a good hike so I’m going to start posting them more! 

This hike is about 3.7 miles round trip and has some very enchanting views😍. For about 1.2 miles it’s a trail with a flat surface where you cross a few streams by walking over logs and through the beautiful Forrest. Once you reach the mountains it becomes a bit more challenging. DONT listen to the signs when you get in the mountains it’ll tell you you’re going the wrong way but you’re not!! Just keep going. You’ll hike for another maybe .8 miles and then you see the beautiful falls😍. 

I went a couple weeks ago and it was beyond beautiful. The leaves are turning colors and the weather was perfect. 
I packed a lunch and brought lots of water, snacks, my journal (and 🍄). 

Lmk how you like it🤍🫶🏽 

#hike #california
